{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":157878,"duration_api_ms":235598,"num_turns":8,"result":"I've thoroughly explored the project. Here's my design for the admin dashboard:\n\n## Design: Admin Dashboard with Metrics & Charts\n\n### Backend — `app/api/dashboard.py`\n\n5 endpoints, all **admin-only** via `require_role(RolUsuario.ADMIN)`:\n\n| Endpoint | Description | Data Source |\n|----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `GET /api/dashboard/stats` | KPI summary cards | Join across Usuario, Pago, Inscripcion, Turno |\n| `GET /api/dashboard/ingresos?periodo=6m` | Monthly revenue trend | Pago (estado=APROBADO), grouped by month |\n| `GET /api/dashboard/actividades-ranking` | Students per activity | Inscripcion (ACTIVA) → Turno → Actividad |\n| `GET /api/dashboard/asistencias-trend` | Weekly attendance trend | Asistencia (presente=true), grouped by week |\n| `GET /api/dashboard/morosos` | Overdue payment list | Pago (estado=VENCIDO) with alumno details |\n\n**Stats response shape:**\n```python\n{\n  \"alumnos_activos\": int,\n  \"alumnos_inactivos\": int,\n  \"nuevos_este_mes\": int,\n  \"ingresos_mes_actual\": float,\n  \"ocupacion_promedio\": float  # avg enrollment/capacity ratio\n}\n```\n\n**Architecture:** Direct queries in the router (no separate service layer for read-only aggregate queries — keeps it simple). All queries are async SQLAlchemy selects with `func.count`, `func.sum`, `func.strftime` for grouping.\n\n### Frontend — `src/pages/admin/Dashboard.tsx`\n\n**Layout (responsive grid):**\n- **Top row:** 5 KPI cards (stats) — 5-col grid on desktop, 2-col on mobile\n- **Second row:** Revenue line chart (Recharts `LineChart`) — full width\n- **Third row:** Activity bar chart + Attendance trend line chart — 2-col\n- **Bottom:** Overdue payments table with student name, plan, amount, due date\n\n**Approach:**\n- Replace the existing placeholder `Dashboard.tsx` with the admin dashboard\n- Use existing `Card` component for KPI cards\